      {
        "name": "Spell Mimic",
        "type": "skill",
        "_id": "C0I6XyrZzGZtbcVK",
        "img": "systems/projectfu/styles/static/compendium/classes/chimerist/chimerist_spell_mimic.png",
        "system": {
          "summary": {
            "value": ""
          },
          "description": "<p>After a <strong>beast</strong>, <strong>monster</strong>, or <strong>plant</strong> creature you can see casts a spell and resolves its effects, you may learn that spell as a <strong>Chimerist</strong> spell of your own: if you do, record the <strong>Species</strong> of the creature you learned it from.</p><p>When you first acquire this Skill, choose <strong>【INS + WLP】</strong> or <strong>【MIG + WLP】</strong>. From now on, your offensive (@ICON[offensive]) <strong>Chimerist</strong> spells will use the chosen Attributes for the Magic Check, regardless of the Attributes used by the creature you learned the spell from.</p><p>You may have <strong>up to 【SL + 2】 different Chimerist spells</strong> memorized this way. If you want to memorize a new <strong>Chimerist</strong> spell but are already at your limit, you must forget one of your old spells and replace it with the new spell.</p><hr /><p>For <strong>spell</strong> breakdown, refer to: @UUID[Compendium.projectfu.handouts.JournalEntry.U0zSlmaK8PDCjMlV]{Spell Rules} or see <strong>Core Rulebook,</strong> page <strong>114</strong>.</p>",
